cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on Online Social Networks (OSNs) and their diffusion phenomenon, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes new sampling approaches for gathering diffusion data, which can be considered a software engineering problem.
3. cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) - The paper deals with social networks and their analysis, which is a key area of computational social science.
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the problem of choosing an appropriate sampling approach, which can be viewed as a data structures and algorithms problem.
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes new characteristics to evaluate sampling approaches, which can be considered an artificial intelligence problem.
